The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing shortest paths in graphs, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Network Information Theory (cs.NI), Algorithmic Mathematics (cs.AL), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper specifically focuses on weighted graphs, which narrows down the sub-categories to cs.DS, cs.AL, and cs.DM. The use of pipelined algorithms and simplification of earlier procedures suggests a focus on distributed computing, which makes cs.DC the most likely category.
